ed_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:35.744902360Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":341,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: benchmark and regression coverage should measure idle-heartbeat overhead, filter selectivity costs, cadence adaptation under churn and degraded sources, and the operational cost difference between durable event publication and ephemeral keepalive traffic.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:06Z"},{"id":345,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Historical-performance follow-up: benchmarks must measure replay and as-of latency, cache-hit versus reconstruction cost, payload-size behavior for historical responses, and SQLite churn introduced by replay caching so the feature stays operationally cheap enough for live debugging.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:28:15Z"},{"id":361,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: benchmark coverage must measure redaction and safe-preview cost on hot surfaces and replay paths so the safety layer remains cheap enough for routine robot consumption.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:28Z"},{"id":370,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: benchmark coverage now explicitly waits for 8.2 so user-facing cost checks include dashboard and alternate-renderer projection work, not only CLI renderers. Measure payload, allocation, and redaction or safe-preview overhead where those projections surface compact evidence.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:40Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add redaction, sensitivity, and disclosure-control verification coverage","description":"Add dedicated verification for sensitivity, redaction, and disclosure-control semantics so ntm can prove richer robot data stay safe across persistence, replay, diagnostics, and transport boundaries.","design":"The tests should cover contract examples for visible versus preview_only versus redacted versus withheld payloads; rule-version and reason markers; safe-preview generation for pane output, mail snippets, diagnostic evidence, and replay snapshots; no-leak guarantees in SQLite projections, attention journals, incident replay caches, REST payloads, and streaming events; allowlisted-field behavior; and explicit diagnostic explanations for why content was transformed. Coverage should include package-local unit tests, SQLite and restart integration tests, Go-based e2e scenarios, and benchmark or regression checks for redaction cost and payload-size effects. Logging should be excellent: scenario name, schema ID, rule version, disclosure state, hidden-field counts, hashed evidence handles, replay mode, and diffs that prove raw secrets were not emitted.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the redesign has explicit automated coverage proving that sensitive material is transformed or withheld consistently across live surfaces, replay, persistence, diagnostics, and parity transports, and when failures produce enough detailed logging that a maintainer can understand exactly what leaked, what was expected, and which rule or surface misbehaved.","notes":"Sensitivity handling is too important to leave as an implied side effect of generic tests. If a regression could leak a secret without a dedicated failing test and clear artifact trail, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.838581790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:46.082586209Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","sensitivity","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:40.673125135Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:41.531532027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:42.403226219Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:43.306247021Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:44.270220056Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:07:55.154188545Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:16.279676807Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:45.281933126Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.838581790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:10:55.404469027Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.11","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.10","type":"blocks","created_at