":"2026-03-26T21:11:55Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.12","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add audit-trail and actor-attribution verification coverage","description":"Add dedicated verification for auditability and actor attribution so the redesign can prove operator-state changes, actuation loops, incident transitions, and disclosure decisions remain traceable across restart, replay, and transport boundaries.","design":"The tests should cover contract examples for actor-attributed attention-state changes, actuation request and outcome trails, incident lifecycle history, audit visibility in diagnostics or inspect flows, and the interaction between sensitivity redaction and audit usefulness. Coverage should include package-local unit tests for store APIs and event shaping, SQLite or restart integration tests for retention and replay behavior, Go-based e2e scenarios where multiple actors or sessions mutate state, and benchmark or regression checks that audit capture does not make hot paths noisy or expensive. Logging should be excellent: actor identifiers, origin classes, request IDs, affected references, timestamps, decision reasons, disclosure states, replay mode, and diffs that explain missing or malformed audit history.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when automated coverage proves that audit-worthy events are persisted and exposed consistently enough that a maintainer can answer who changed this, what request caused this effect, and why this disclosure or override happened, with detailed logs when any part of that trail breaks.","notes":"Auditability is a product feature here, not compliance theater. If a failure can erase or obscure operator trust history without a focused failing test, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.309450111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985831755Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:43:09.985369821Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented. audit_validation_test.go (494 lines): TestAuditEventStructure, ActorIDFormats, AttentionAcknowledge, AttentionSnooze, ActuationSend, ActuationInterrupt, IncidentCreate/Escalate/Resolve, DisclosureRedact, QueryByActor, QueryByTargetRef, RetentionPolicy, RedactionDoesNotObscureActor. audit_attribution_test.go (778 lines): ActorAttributionOnAttentionStateChange, ActuationRequestOutcomeTrail, IncidentLifecycleHistory, VisibleInDiagnostics, SensitivityRedactionPreservesUsefulness, MultiActorSessionMutation, PersistenceAcrossRestart. Full acceptance criteria coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.12","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.309450111Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add SQLite, adapter, degraded-source, and restart-recovery integration tests","description":"Add integration coverage for the runtime projection store, adapter normalization, degraded-source handling, attention replay, watermark persistence, incident evolution, and restart recovery behavior. This task exists because the hardest parts of the redesign live at the seams between subsystems, not inside isolated helper functions.","design":"The tests should exercise realistic sequences such as source outage followed by partial recovery, ntm restart followed by resumed delta computation, incident promotion after repeated evidence, projection rebuild with durable cursor continuity, ambiguous timeout followed by safe retry, duplicate request suppression with later verified outcome, repeated flapping source with cooldown and resurfacing, acknowledgment followed by material change and resurfacing, snooze expiry, pin and manual escalation behavior, retention or pruning decisions, and partial transport resync. They should use the shared deterministic harness and log scenario IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor transitions, watermark state, source_health changes, operator-state transitions, suppression or resurfacing markers, incident fingerprints, and assertion diffs with enough detail to diagnose failures quickly. This task should prove the redesign works as an operational system, not just as a collection of structs.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the critical persistence, degradation, replay, restart-safety, retry-safety, attention-hygiene, and operator-control promises of the redesign are pinned by deterministic integration tests that emit rich debugging context and fail loudly when those promises regress.","notes":"Future self: if you ever want to simplify something 'just for now,' make sure these tests still express the product promises that matter.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:27.316098652Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:24.883033873Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["integration","robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:26:19.161234835Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:52.934763148Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:17.490511841Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:16.320725277Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:16.842076218Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:36.296941786Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:17.376897885Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:26:20.009095793Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:04.649122301Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:09.455231992Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}"